{"id": 7717, "title": "Ticket #7717: Clean up ProcAPI", "description": "<blockquote>\nImproving the ProcAPI code for macOS revealed some additional improvements that could be made that weren't ready in time for the same release.\n\n<p>Highlights:\n</p><ul>\n<li>Change <code>pidList</code> from a linked list to a vector.\n</li><li>Remove solaris code.\n</li><li>Remove <code>buildPidList()</code> for macOS and move calls into <code>buildProcInfoList()</code> on linux.</li></ul>\n</blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2020-Jun-30 19:52</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/8e263fee69d5663d2a59705932a61d9bb0a79566\">[60046]</a></span>: Remove solaris code in <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=ProcApi\" title=\"Proc Api\">ProcApi</a></span>. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=7717\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('7717'); return false;\" title=\"Clean up ProcAPI\">#7717</a></span>  (By Jaime Frey )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2020-Jun-30 19:52</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/15a252bd88005f654cbdbe05cf5b6a4bdfb94fb4\">[60045]</a></span>: Turn ProcAPI::buildPidList() into a more internal function. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=7717\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('7717'); return false;\" title=\"Clean up ProcAPI\">#7717</a></span> buildPidList() is only used for buildProcInfoList() and must always preceed it, on those platforms that use it. So put the call inside buildPidList().  (By Jaime Frey )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2020-Jun-30 19:51</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/d611b700cd605a68703e0660b14994bf34e7efcb\">[60044]</a></span>: Change ProcAPI::pidList to a vector. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=7717\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('7717'); return false;\" title=\"Clean up ProcAPI\">#7717</a></span> This greatly reduces the number of memory allocations.  (By Jaime Frey )</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>", "type": "enhance", "last_change": "2020-Jul-02 10:08", "status": "resolved", "created": "2020-Jun-29 14:52", "fixed_version": "2020-Jun-29 14:52", "broken_version": "", "priority": "3", "subsystem": "Libs", "assigned_to": "jfrey", "derived_from": "#7708", "creator": "jfrey", "rust": "", "customer_group": "other", "visibility": "public", "notify": "", "due_date": ""}